I was on a long flight from Shenzhen to LA, and like many travelers, I decided to catch up on some movies. Among the selections was Oppenheimer. One particular line in the movie struck me:
&ldquo;Algebra is like a score. The question is not &lsquo;can you read the music?&rsquo; but &lsquo;can you hear it?&rsquo;&rdquo;
Oppenheimer’s response was quick and simple:
&ldquo;Yes. I can hear it.&rdquo;
In that moment, I couldn’t help but reflect on the comparison between algebra and music.

